name: Sevy | Monika Fox
description:
Trained Model of gorgeous Monika Fox.

I trained this model with almost 5000 high-res images for a total of 134 hours (about 5 days and 1/2) thanks to a Google Colab Pro+ account since my 3090 Ti would be dead after such a training.

Therefore please consider to

A good way to use this model is to give a full sentence at the beginning and keeping the prompt as clean as possible

Prompt:
1girl, beach, blonde_hair, blue_eyes, bra, breasts, choker, cleavage, lips, long_hair, looking_at_viewer, medium_breasts, necklace, photorealistic, realistic, solo, underwear, upper_body

Example:
a woman in a blue bra posing for a picture with her hands on her hips and her right hand on her hip, 1girl, beach, blonde_hair, blue_eyes, bra, breasts, choker, cleavage, lips, long_hair, looking_at_viewer, medium_breasts, necklace, photorealistic, realistic, solo, underwear, upper_body

Negative Prompt:
illustration, 3d, sepia, painting, cartoons, sketch, (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, normal quality, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale:1.2)), penis, newhalf, collapsed eyeshadow, multiple eyebrows, vaginas in breasts,holes on breasts, fleckles, stretched nipples, gigantic penis, nipples on buttocks, analog, analog photo, signature, logo, 2 faces

Example:
use as it is, but consider giving more parenthesized weight to things you don't want to be displayed like (car:1.5), ((1boy:2)), (dress:1) etc...

Usual Settings:
Model: Monika-Fox_v1.0-fp32-no-ema (obviously!)
Steps: 75
Sampler: DPM++ SDE or DPM++ 2M Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras v2
CFG scale => between 8 and 15
Seed: random
Face restoration: CodeFormer
Size: 512x512
Model hash: e54b55f70d
Denoising strength: 0.5 to 0.75
Hires upscale: 1,5 or 2
Hires upscaler: Latent

Feel free to experiment and let me know your opinion. And if you like it please

Let me thank hallatore the creator of quality improvements to DPM++ 2M Karras sampling named DPM++ 2M Karras v2
More info on
Reddit post: https://www.reddit.com/r/StableDiffusion/comments/11mulj6/quality_improvements_to_dpm_2m_karras_sampling/

and

Github discussion: https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/discussions/8457

Have fun!
